00:31:59.380 --> 00:32:03.010 align:middle line:84%
And when he met
his father again,

00:32:03.010 --> 00:32:06.700 align:middle line:84%
his father was
not a man anymore.

00:32:06.700 --> 00:32:10.030 align:middle line:90%
He was the awakened one.

00:32:10.030 --> 00:32:13.150 align:middle line:84%
We can't even picture
or imagine what

00:32:13.150 --> 00:32:15.010 align:middle line:90%
this meeting would be about.

00:32:15.010 --> 00:32:18.735 align:middle line:84%
A very conflicted
young man meeting

00:32:18.735 --> 00:32:20.860 align:middle line:84%
the father who abandoned
him and then in the moment

00:32:20.860 --> 00:32:23.020 align:middle line:84%
that he meets him,
he sees something

00:32:23.020 --> 00:32:28.870 align:middle line:84%
in the eyes of this being
that it's not of this world

00:32:28.870 --> 00:32:30.610 align:middle line:90%
anymore, right?

00:32:30.610 --> 00:32:32.710 align:middle line:84%
Well, unluckily we
don't know the details

00:32:32.710 --> 00:32:35.230 align:middle line:84%
of the story, which I
like to fill in in my mind

00:32:35.230 --> 00:32:38.920 align:middle line:84%
but what we know is
that the Buddha gave

00:32:38.920 --> 00:32:41.380 align:middle line:84%
to Rahula a teaching
which became

00:32:41.380 --> 00:32:44.470 align:middle line:90%
one of the pillars of Dharma.

00:32:44.470 --> 00:32:47.530 align:middle line:84%
This teaching is called
the Brahma-viharas,

00:32:47.530 --> 00:32:50.470 align:middle line:90%
the abodes of creation.

00:32:50.470 --> 00:32:53.560 align:middle line:84%
Brahma means the
